Chicago Bulls Beat Indiana Pacers 104-99 in Opening Game of NBA Playoffs

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-04-16T19:50:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-16/chicago-bulls-beat-indiana-pacers-104-99-in-opening-game-of-nba-playoffs.html
The  Chicago Bulls  rallied to beat
the  Indiana  Pacers 104-99 in the opening game of the National
Basketball Association playoffs.  Derrick Rose  scored 39 points to lead the Bulls at the
United Center in  Chicago . Luol Deng added 18 points and 10
rebounds for Chicago, which outscored Indiana 33-20 in the
fourth quarter.  Danny Granger scored 24 points for Indiana. Chicago hosts
Game 2 in the best-of-seven Eastern Conference series in two
days.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  